## Harness map

This project follows the agentic-blueprint five-stage lifecycle
(**Research & Think → Plan → Build → Ship → Run**). The Claude Code
harness is in `.claude/` — copy it wholesale from the blueprint's
`claude-config/.claude/`:

| Primitive | Location | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Slash commands | `.claude/commands/` | `/research`, `/plan`, `/build`, `/ship`, `/run`, `/stage`, `/new-feature` |
| Subagents | `.claude/agents/` | `researcher`, `spec-writer`, `spec-reviewer`, `starter-verifier`, `docs-inspector` |
| Skills | `.claude/skills/` | `australian-spelling`, `spec-author`, `hard-rules-check`, `changelog-entry`, `memory-sync` |
| Hooks | `.claude/hooks/` | `session-start`, `stage-aware-prompt`, `template-guard`, `pre-write-spelling`, `pre-commit-gate` |
| Settings | `.claude/settings.json` | Permissions + hook wiring |

When in doubt, run `/stage` for a read-only snapshot of where you are.

