## Meta-principles

Three architectural principles shape how the harness itself is built.
Unlike the Hard Rules, these are not machine-checked — they are lenses
for deciding how new commands, agents, skills, and hooks should behave.

10. **Progressive disclosure.** Commands and agents load only the context
    they need, on demand. Skills expose a short `SKILL.md` and defer
    reference material until it's actually asked for.
11. **Context economy.** Every token spent on framing is a token not spent
    on the task. Prefer terse primitives, dense tables, and delegated
    subagents over long inline prose.
12. **Gates over guidance.** When a rule matters, enforce it with a hook
    or CI check. Guidance in docs degrades over time; gates don't.

Full rationale for all twelve principles lives in the blueprint's
[`docs/principles/`](https://github.com/parkjadev/agentic-blueprint/tree/main/docs/principles).

